You can also use a for loop to remove elements from an array in a more general way. Here's an example:
```js
for (let i = arr.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
  if (arr[i] === someValue) {
    arr.splice(i, 1); // Removes the element at index i and returns its index and length
    break; // Stops the loop when the value is found and removed
  } else {
    // Continue iterating through the array if the value is not found yet
  }
}
```
